1
00:00:02,120 --> 00:00:03,359
I'm not carrying you back.

2
00:00:04,559 --> 00:00:06,120
I'm not going back.

3
00:00:06,719 --> 00:00:08,480
You can pack my bags and bring them here.

4
00:00:08,519 --> 00:00:10,080
I'm staying at Teacher Fu's.

5
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:11,800
Mmm.

6
00:00:15,679 --> 00:00:17,919
This is Teacher Feng.

7
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:20,096
These are the two college
students who came to volunteer here.

8
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:21,160
Here's to you.

9
00:00:28,480 --> 00:00:29,919
Teacher Fu, a toast to you.

10
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:31,199
Hello, Chairman Ye.

11
00:00:31,320 --> 00:00:32,920
You're just in time.

12
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:33,719
Let me introduce you.

13
00:00:33,743 --> 00:00:35,863
This is Chairman Ye, the
head of our Tea Association.

14
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,960
A pleasure to meet you. Hello.

15
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,200
Let's drink together.

16
00:00:42,479 --> 00:00:43,479
Enjoy your meal.

17
00:00:49,079 --> 00:00:51,119
Come on, another one. Stand up. Come on.

18
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:52,976
My brother says he's not
going back to your place.

19
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,520
He wants me to bring his luggage over.

20
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,280
I know.

21
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:09,000
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

22
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:16,500
(Episode 4: Life Path)

23
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,400
Sister Lan.

24
00:03:51,879 --> 00:03:53,520
Was I a bit too much?

25
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,319
When you're drunk, yes.

26
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,878
But when I don't get a response,

27
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:03,280
I tend to act like this.

28
00:04:04,680 --> 00:04:05,960
Another Shi Yuhao.

29
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,280
It's different.

30
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:10,360
He doesn't run away.

31
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:13,280
He just doesn't need me.

32
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,399
Liking someone isn't about
making them need you.

33
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,399
Let liking just be liking.

34
00:04:20,519 --> 00:04:21,879
Don't turn it into a need.

35
00:04:42,572 --> 00:04:45,699
[Let liking just be liking.]

36
00:04:49,339 --> 00:04:50,932
[Love "You" [Honorific]]

37
00:05:02,192 --> 00:05:04,399
What happened between
you and my brother last night?

38
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:07,079
He asked me if I like men.

39
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:08,800
And the truth is?

40
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:09,959
It's not important.

41
00:05:12,079 --> 00:05:14,319
Answering like that would
definitely trigger my brother.

42
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:16,720
My brother hates vague answers.

43
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,279
It really isn't important.

44
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,720
It's like these tea plants.

45
00:05:20,879 --> 00:05:21,879
The experts come,

46
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:23,495
measure how many meters
the roots go into the ground,

47
00:05:23,519 --> 00:05:24,519
collect a bunch of data,

48
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:27,600
but in the end, isn't it all judged
by whether the tea tastes good?

49
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,120
Be practical.

50
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,600
A kilogram, a ton,

51
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,175
no matter how much tea, it
all has to be picked leaf by leaf.

52
00:05:36,199 --> 00:05:39,279
A lot of things that are set in stone
can only be changed one step at a time.

53
00:05:45,399 --> 00:05:46,600
Are you serious?

54
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:09,360
I'm selling tea tomorrow.

55
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:13,279
I need to know how tea
gets from the tree to the cup.

56
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:17,199
Didn't you get a taste of it yesterday?

57
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:21,039
Experiencing it and doing
it are two different things.

58
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:23,959
I want to make a batch of
my own tea from start to finish.

59
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,600
I'm heading to the fields.

60
00:06:40,519 --> 00:06:41,999
After you eat, I'll take you to work.

61
00:08:41,519 --> 00:08:42,399
Tomorrow is the Dragon-Elephant Festival.

62
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,480
So eat more meat tonight.

63
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,056
You really can't eat meat during
the Dragon-Elephant Festival?

64
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,279
And you can't 'ku-ku-ku'.

65
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:51,500
What does that mean?

66
00:08:51,559 --> 00:08:53,279
Ask him, he doesn't know anything.

67
00:08:54,559 --> 00:08:55,519
Come on, another one.

68
00:08:55,559 --> 00:08:56,559
Come on, come on.

69
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:00,519
Hey.

70
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,760
We're wrapping up filming soon.

71
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:05,759
Do you have classes when
you go back to school?

72
00:09:06,519 --> 00:09:08,480
No, I have to rehearse
for the graduation play.

73
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:11,480
You'll probably have to help
with promoting our show, right?

74
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:12,919
Mmm-hmm.

75
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,040
Our company's post-production is very fast.

76
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:16,600
It can be released in two months.

77
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:20,120
The promotion will probably start
before those two months are up.

78
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Oh.

79
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:24,600
I think we could create some buzz.

80
00:09:25,679 --> 00:09:26,679
Like what?

81
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:30,399
Like getting 'secretly' photographed
while shopping together.

82
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,960
A lot of CPs use this trick.

83
00:09:36,879 --> 00:09:38,119
You know a lot about this, huh?

84
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,879
I did some research.

85
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,919
I'm a fast learner.

86
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,720
When are you leaving?

87
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:12,120
Are you eager for me to leave?

88
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,080
Yeah.

89
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,000
With you here, I can't focus on work.

90
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,080
You seem to be doing just fine to me.

91
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,480
I'm faking it.

92
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:47,080
If you don't leave soon,

93
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:49,919
I really won't be able to keep it up.

94
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:57,360
I like men.

95
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:06,759
Is your name 'Men'?

96
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,879
I triggered you.

97
00:11:54,919 --> 00:11:55,919
No.

98
00:11:58,279 --> 00:11:59,879
You make me feel completely at peace.

99
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:04,519
You've never abandoned me.

100
00:12:54,279 --> 00:12:55,879
I'll save this batch of tea for you.

101
00:12:56,799 --> 00:12:57,799
I'll save it till I die.

102
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:08,359
What on earth does 'no ku-ku-ku'
during the Dragon-Elephant Festival mean?

103
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:17,120
It's true. All the locals believe it.

104
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:22,720
So what happens if you break the rule?

105
00:13:23,759 --> 00:13:24,879
You want to break it?

106
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,360
Get lost.

107
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:35,080
Use that to scoop it up.

108
00:13:35,159 --> 00:13:36,159
That's about enough.

109
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,360
Just use that to store it. Store it.

110
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:41,919
Come on.

111
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:58,879
The roasting is done. I'm going
to shower first. I'm dying of heat.

112
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:01,519
Hey, it's not over yet.

113
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,200
You knead it for me.

114
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,720
You'd do anything for money.

115
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:39,519
I'm almost as tan as you.

116
00:14:42,919 --> 00:14:43,919
Your face is still okay.

117
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,519
My stylist is coming tomorrow.

118
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,720
You want me to stay away?

119
00:14:57,272 --> 00:14:58,872
I want to introduce you to him.

120
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:00,720
I'm not the one doing a livestream.

121
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,120
Sister Lan, you should know.

122
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:10,936
Sister Jialin and Sister Lan are
the ones who launched my career.

123
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:12,560
They're closer to me than my own mother.

124
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,080
So you want to introduce
me to your parents?

125
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,080
I do.

126
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:31,559
Bro, Sister Jialin is here.

127
00:16:05,279 --> 00:16:06,279
Sister Jialin.

128
00:16:12,519 --> 00:16:13,759
Shi Yuhao posted it.

129
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,320
He hasn't left Molie yet.

130
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,000
The reservoir.

131
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:33,960
Right.

132
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,279
This is a good picture.

133
00:16:37,759 --> 00:16:38,799
I'm saving it.

134
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,919
Qinglang, do you have any idea
what the repercussions of this are?

135
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:48,840
Shi Yuhao wants to
create a CP ship with me.

136
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,720
He posts one blurry photo,

137
00:16:50,759 --> 00:16:51,919
so just let him post it.

138
00:16:52,519 --> 00:16:54,279
Who can tell that's me and Changyang?

139
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,200
It doesn't matter who's in that photo.

140
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:59,399
That photo points directly at you.

141
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,720
If you publicly announce that you're gay,

142
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:04,999
your career in the entertainment
industry will be over.

143
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Shi Yuhao is dragging you down with him.

144
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,680
Is it worth it to be destroyed by him?

145
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,295
If it weren't for the random Weibo posts
you've been making these past few days,

146
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,920
this would be easy to clear up.

147
00:17:18,559 --> 00:17:20,639
But now, all the details
have been woven into a web,

148
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,599
and there's no room
left for you to explain.

149
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,799
Then I won't explain.
I'll make it official.

150
00:17:27,799 --> 00:17:30,160
You spent seven years climbing
to the top of the mountain,

151
00:17:30,279 --> 00:17:32,319
just to jump off and kill yourself?

152
00:17:33,319 --> 00:17:35,318
Qinglang, you're a celebrity.

153
00:17:35,319 --> 00:17:37,400
How many endorsement contracts do you have?

154
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:39,720
You took this job.

155
00:17:40,079 --> 00:17:41,159
You have to see it through.

156
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:44,559
You can't just walk away
from it whenever you feel like it.

157
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,720
Changyang, come with me.

158
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,000
What's up with you two?

159
00:18:00,960 --> 00:18:02,680
This is grown-up business. Don't ask.

160
00:18:04,279 --> 00:18:05,279
Tell me.

161
00:18:05,519 --> 00:18:06,519
Come on.

162
00:18:07,519 --> 00:18:08,519
Tell me.

163
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:38,079
Xu Changyang, your brother is Wenshu.

164
00:18:39,079 --> 00:18:40,159
Half-brothers, same father.

165
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:44,559
You met Qingtian through Wenshu.

166
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,656
Qingtian wanted to come to the mountains.

167
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,079
Wenshu introduced me to him.

168
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,160
And Qinglang?

169
00:18:52,519 --> 00:18:54,479
Qinglang said he wanted to find
a quiet place to stay for a few days.

170
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:55,896
I told him to come to the mountains.

171
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,319
To come to Molie with Qingtian.

172
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:59,120
You're very precise with your words.

173
00:18:59,319 --> 00:19:00,319
Airtight.

174
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,279
I have nothing to hide.

175
00:19:03,119 --> 00:19:05,319
So, in just a few days,

176
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:06,359
Qinglang fell in love with you,

177
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:07,560
and you fell in love with him.

178
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:10,480
Yes.

179
00:19:10,519 --> 00:19:12,558
Lies. You know who he is.

180
00:19:12,559 --> 00:19:13,960
How dare you take this step?

181
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,919
With your depth of thought,

182
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,800
this couldn't have
happened in just a few days.

183
00:19:18,319 --> 00:19:20,480
Tell me. How much money do you want?

184
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:23,519
Or, how much did Shi Yuhao promise you?

185
00:19:25,559 --> 00:19:27,400
Does everything have
to be defined by money?

186
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:30,680
What in this world
doesn't have a price tag?

187
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,279
Don't talk to me about love.

188
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:34,480
At your age, you don't understand.

189
00:19:42,519 --> 00:19:44,598
I have to go over the livestream
plan with Qingtian tonight.

190
00:19:44,599 --> 00:19:45,599
I'm staying at his place.

191
00:19:45,960 --> 00:19:46,960
I know.

192
00:20:15,119 --> 00:20:16,358
After the livestream tomorrow,

193
00:20:16,359 --> 00:20:18,055
Sister Lan wants you to
come back to the set with me.

194
00:20:18,079 --> 00:20:18,960
We're about to wrap.

195
00:20:18,961 --> 00:20:20,201
We need you for a cameo anyway.

196
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:24,880
Qinglang?

197
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,319
That Changyang is impressive.

198
00:20:32,319 --> 00:20:34,119
20 years old, clear logic,

199
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:35,519
precise expression.

200
00:20:36,119 --> 00:20:38,400
Qinglang wasn't half as sharp at his age.

201
00:20:40,759 --> 00:20:42,319
Is he one of Shi Yuhao's people?

202
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:44,880
Doesn't seem like it.

203
00:20:45,359 --> 00:20:46,720
But people are hard to read.

204
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,680
I've only met him once.
I can't see through him.

205
00:20:50,599 --> 00:20:51,599
Also,

206
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:54,199
just now, I told Qinglang to come
back to the set with me tomorrow.

207
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,200
He didn't respond.

208
00:20:56,519 --> 00:20:57,720
If you don't come to Molie,

209
00:20:58,359 --> 00:20:59,920
no one can bring him back.

210
00:21:01,056 --> 00:21:02,656
Let's finish the livestream first.

211
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,920
We can use this charity
event to salvage public opinion.

212
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:10,880
Sister Lan, the makeup
artists are here for touch-ups.

213
00:21:13,319 --> 00:21:15,079
Let's check your hair.

214
00:21:17,920 --> 00:21:20,200
Don't make the hair too
dramatic. Keep it natural.

215
00:21:21,279 --> 00:21:22,279
Okay.

216
00:21:26,279 --> 00:21:29,799
You and Shi Yuhao never did
anything this ridiculous back then.

217
00:21:31,559 --> 00:21:32,720
Is it that ridiculous?

218
00:21:34,119 --> 00:21:35,318
It's all over the trending topics.

219
00:21:35,319 --> 00:21:36,399
How is that not ridiculous?

220
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,680
Before, you'd run your Weibo
posts by the company first,

221
00:21:41,599 --> 00:21:43,319
or ask for Sister Lan's opinion.

222
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,119
Do you have other plans now?

223
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:49,120
Or do you want to stay in the
mountains and be a tea farmer?

224
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:52,799
That's not out of the question.

225
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:54,440
I've learned how to do it all anyway.

226
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,880
Picking and roasting tea.

227
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,720
If the livestream sales go well,

228
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,800
I'll just sell tea on
livestreams from now on.

229
00:22:03,759 --> 00:22:05,679
Did you eat too many
mushrooms and get poisoned?

230
00:22:06,079 --> 00:22:07,359
Termite mushrooms are poisonous.

231
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:17,319
Bro, the host will go over
the rundown with you in a bit.

232
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:20,990
[Qinglang is asking Changyang
to arrange the wrap party dinner]

233
00:22:21,079 --> 00:22:22,079
Hello?

234
00:22:22,319 --> 00:22:23,319
Oh, okay.

235
00:22:47,319 --> 00:22:48,319
Handsome.

236
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:51,480
What are you doing?

237
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:53,319
Waiting for your livestream.

238
00:22:53,559 --> 00:22:54,936
I'll give you a secret signal later.

239
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,520
When you see it, post a comment for me.

240
00:22:59,000 --> 00:22:59,920
There are so many people.

241
00:22:59,921 --> 00:23:01,079
Will you be able to find me?

242
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,880
Yes. I'll have Qingtian screen-record it.

243
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,560
I'll look for it after the stream.

244
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:15,920
Hey, babe.

245
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:19,159
Hey, get a few more phone numbers later.

246
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,760
And register a few more TikTok accounts.

247
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,519
Then use the name Ji
Zongjun for all of them.

248
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:26,480
Ji as in 'machine.'

249
00:23:26,599 --> 00:23:27,680
Jun as in 'handsome.'

250
00:23:28,119 --> 00:23:30,480
And the 'Zong' in the
middle is as in 'to track.'

251
00:23:33,079 --> 00:23:37,399
After that, go to Qinglang's livestream.

252
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:39,079
And post comments in his comment section.

253
00:23:39,319 --> 00:23:40,680
Just pretend to be his fan.

254
00:23:43,079 --> 00:23:47,400
The content should be, uh,
stuff like 'I love you, ' 'I like you.'

255
00:23:47,519 --> 00:23:48,359
'Wow, so handsome.'

256
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:49,920
Things like that.

257
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:53,680
Oh, during the livestream,
he's going to make a...

258
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:54,799
uhh, a hand gesture.

259
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:55,880
I'll send it to you then.

260
00:23:56,319 --> 00:23:57,680
I'll forward it to you in a bit.

261
00:23:58,119 --> 00:24:01,599
And when he makes that
gesture, you have to post.

262
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:03,559
Okay?

263
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:05,936
So I should just keep spamming the
comments with the Ji Zongjun accounts?

264
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:07,759
Yep. Love you, babe.

265
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,519
Teacher Ye, this is my brother.

266
00:24:17,079 --> 00:24:18,079
Oh, hello.

267
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,200
Hello, Teacher Ye.

268
00:24:19,319 --> 00:24:20,279
That's right.

269
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:21,679
Let's see, we'll basically...

270
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:22,079
Teacher Ye.

271
00:24:22,079 --> 00:24:22,680
Yes?

272
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,519
The factory director is looking for you.

273
00:24:23,559 --> 00:24:24,400
Oh, okay, okay.

274
00:24:24,519 --> 00:24:24,960
Excuse me.

275
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:25,960
Pardon me for a moment.

276
00:24:30,890 --> 00:24:33,710
[Changyang: What does the
gesture you just made mean?]

277
00:24:36,363 --> 00:24:39,469
[Figure it out yourself]

278
00:24:42,430 --> 00:24:44,996
You suck to the core. Am I right?

279
00:24:45,020 --> 00:24:47,160
[I'm right, aren't I?]

280
00:24:50,863 --> 00:24:52,143
[Setting off firecrackers [???]]

281
00:24:53,079 --> 00:24:54,079
Go on, laugh.

282
00:24:55,279 --> 00:24:56,896
Is it too late to back out
of the livestream now?

283
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:57,920
Too late.

284
00:24:58,519 --> 00:24:59,919
Then you have to
screen-record for me later.

285
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:00,680
What for?

286
00:25:00,681 --> 00:25:02,279
If you don't, I'm not doing the stream.

287
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,559
Everyone, we have five minutes.

288
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:06,720
Teacher Ye.

289
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,160
Sorry to interrupt.

290
00:25:10,599 --> 00:25:11,879
Let's continue our run-through.

291
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:14,519
Okay, everyone, look up and
check the lighting on your faces.

292
00:25:19,119 --> 00:25:22,319
Welcome, everyone, to the
Molie Tea Plantation livestream.

293
00:25:22,559 --> 00:25:24,758
Today, we're very lucky to have invited

294
00:25:24,759 --> 00:25:26,880
a fellow tea lover to our livestream.

295
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:28,720
Hello, everyone.

296
00:25:28,799 --> 00:25:31,799
I'm happy to meet you all
here on 'A Taste of Time.'

297
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,719
The setting for today's
livestream is so beautiful.

298
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:35,078
Before we officially begin,

299
00:25:35,079 --> 00:25:37,920
I have to show everyone the
tea mountains in the distance.

300
00:25:39,319 --> 00:25:42,079
I remember you like a
book about tea mountains.

301
00:25:42,559 --> 00:25:44,799
'A Winter Sun Wakes the
Wind in Spring Hills' Dream.'

302
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,160
Yes.

303
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:47,519
My distant tea mountains,

304
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,575
watching their sea from
thousands of miles away.

305
00:25:49,599 --> 00:25:51,318
The comment section is already flooded.

306
00:25:51,319 --> 00:25:53,359
Wow, so many fans are named Ji Zongjun.

307
00:25:53,599 --> 00:25:56,079
Then let's introduce
today's seven types of tea.

308
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:56,799
Sounds good.

309
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:59,680
Then Teacher Ye will have to
tell me the story behind each tea.

310
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:02,000
Let's start with the simplest one.

311
00:26:02,480 --> 00:26:04,799
Dongguo has a tragic
and beautiful love story.

312
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,119
Legend has it there was a
young couple in the village.

313
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,200
The girl left the village for school.

314
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,519
The boy stayed behind to grow tea.

315
00:26:11,799 --> 00:26:13,920
Their paths diverged from that day on.

316
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,079
They never crossed again.

317
00:26:15,519 --> 00:26:19,079
Later, the boy named
the tea he grew 'Dongguo.'

318
00:26:19,279 --> 00:26:20,896
It means that after
experiencing separation,

319
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:22,559
and understanding life's many trials,

320
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,960
only then can you know how
precious it is to be together.

321
00:26:25,319 --> 00:26:26,920
Daxue Mountain, as its name suggests,

322
00:26:27,079 --> 00:26:28,920
is pure and clean, without a speck of dust.

323
00:26:29,079 --> 00:26:31,880
It preserves a pristine, primeval forest.

324
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:34,720
The thousand-year-old Tea
King Tree is in Daxue Mountain.

325
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,000
Molie.

326
00:26:37,519 --> 00:26:39,559
Xigui, Dongguo.

327
00:26:43,319 --> 00:26:44,400
Daxue Mountain.

328
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:47,319
Yiwu, Nanpo.

329
00:26:47,920 --> 00:26:48,920
Lao Man'e.

330
00:26:50,079 --> 00:26:52,519
Incredible. Teacher Feng,
you know all of them.

331
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,200
I had an expert guiding me.

332
00:26:56,079 --> 00:26:57,920
An expert? What kind of expert?

333
00:26:58,680 --> 00:26:59,759
Hello, Teacher Ye.

334
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:01,400
Hi, Yuhao. Hello.

335
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:02,880
Qinglang.

336
00:27:05,319 --> 00:27:07,960
My signal is a bit weak
over here. Hello, everyone.

337
00:27:09,359 --> 00:27:12,518
I'm here now at the
thousand-year-old Tea King Tree.

338
00:27:12,519 --> 00:27:13,720
Let me show you all.

339
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,199
Wow, it's breathtaking.

340
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:19,000
I feel... I feel that compared to it,

341
00:27:20,279 --> 00:27:21,799
we are all just travellers in time.

342
00:27:45,319 --> 00:27:46,319
What's going on?

343
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,000
Who connected the call?

344
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:53,656
Tang Chen said she touched it by mistake.

345
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:54,680
And you believe that?

346
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,960
Check... check her social media accounts.

347
00:27:57,519 --> 00:27:59,696
Who's going to take responsibility
for a livestream accident like this?

348
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,160
I will. It was my negligence.

349
00:28:01,880 --> 00:28:04,519
She must be a fan of Shi Yuhao.

350
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:06,656
He's like a ghost that won't go away.

351
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:07,920
And also, Teacher Ye.

352
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:18,920
Hello.

353
00:28:18,960 --> 00:28:21,920
We need to arrange
tonight's banquet properly.

354
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:23,319
Okay.

355
00:28:23,319 --> 00:28:23,759
Thank you.

356
00:28:23,759 --> 00:28:24,559
Thanks.

357
00:28:24,599 --> 00:28:25,400
My brother is tired.

358
00:28:25,519 --> 00:28:26,319
I'm very happy.

359
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:27,000
My brother is tired.

360
00:28:27,001 --> 00:28:28,359
Let him rest for a bit.

361
00:28:29,079 --> 00:28:30,919
When the tea farmers
saw your livestream data,

362
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:31,920
they all cried.

363
00:28:32,759 --> 00:28:34,279
I know everyone has worked hard.

364
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,118
You've worked even harder than us.

365
00:28:36,119 --> 00:28:36,880
Ah, thank you, thank you.

366
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:37,961
It's nothing, it's nothing.

367
00:28:38,119 --> 00:28:39,759
We're leaving now. Let's go.

368
00:28:41,759 --> 00:28:42,759
Take care.

369
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:43,759
Okay, thank you.

370
00:28:43,759 --> 00:28:44,759
Okay, okay.

371
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:58,399
We'll be going then. You all get some rest.

372
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,879
Okay, take care.

373
00:28:59,880 --> 00:29:00,880
Okay.

374
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:02,799
Bye-bye.

375
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:04,359
See you later. Get some good rest.

376
00:29:04,960 --> 00:29:06,118
Let's all pack up. Everyone, pack up.

377
00:29:06,119 --> 00:29:07,200
Let's go.

378
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:24,319
Teacher Ye.

379
00:29:24,319 --> 00:29:24,720
Yes?

380
00:29:24,721 --> 00:29:26,801
You knew Shi Yuhao was
going to call in, didn't you?

381
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,719
He came to me this morning

382
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,335
and said you had
arranged for him to call in.

383
00:29:30,359 --> 00:29:32,880
I was vaguely aware of his 'CP'
relationship with Teacher Feng.

384
00:29:33,119 --> 00:29:34,799
The director just wanted to sell more tea.

385
00:29:36,519 --> 00:29:38,599
You should have at
least told us in advance.

386
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,000
You people don't understand
how fandoms work at all.

387
00:30:02,359 --> 00:30:03,359
Where are you?

388
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:05,319
Still at the venue.

389
00:30:06,759 --> 00:30:08,559
Is there still a celebration
banquet tonight?

390
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,160
Yes.

391
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,000
Enemies on all sides.

392
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:15,000
And you're laughing?

393
00:30:16,079 --> 00:30:17,376
You backed out of the variety show.

394
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:19,280
Of course he'd try to
sabotage your livestream.

395
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:21,960
Just handle things tonight. Wait for me.

396
00:30:23,519 --> 00:30:25,079
Let's see how you're going to get here.

397
00:30:25,319 --> 00:30:26,400
I'll fly over.

398
00:30:37,519 --> 00:30:38,319
Master.

399
00:30:38,359 --> 00:30:39,359
Hey.

400
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:47,640
Send me the screen recording.

401
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,400
The video file is a bit big.

402
00:30:48,401 --> 00:30:49,518
I'll send it to you from my
cloud drive when I get back.

403
00:30:49,519 --> 00:30:51,000
No, I want to see it now.

404
00:30:52,359 --> 00:30:53,359
Are you okay?

405
00:30:53,799 --> 00:30:54,799
Couldn't be better.

406
00:30:55,559 --> 00:30:57,079
That was a dirty move by Shi Yuhao.

407
00:30:57,519 --> 00:30:59,095
He's got even dirtier tricks up his sleeve.

408
00:30:59,119 --> 00:31:01,255
I noticed the comment
section was full of 'Ji Zongjun.'

409
00:31:01,279 --> 00:31:02,079
He must have arranged it.

410
00:31:02,079 --> 00:31:02,799
Is Shi Yuhao that desperate now?

411
00:31:02,799 --> 00:31:03,559
Why does he have to cling to my brother?

412
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:04,798
There's a fan on Weibo called Ji Zongjun.

413
00:31:04,799 --> 00:31:06,679
The CP fans all think it's Shi
Yuhao's alternate account.

414
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,295
He hasn't been doing
well since they 'un-coupled.'

415
00:31:08,319 --> 00:31:09,519
You know what a scumbag he is.

416
00:31:09,799 --> 00:31:10,919
He has tons of boyfriends and girlfriends.

417
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,199
If, at that moment, the real

418
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,598
Ji Zongjun had spoken in the comments,

419
00:31:13,599 --> 00:31:15,295
I heard he had a girlfriend
a couple of years ago

420
00:31:15,319 --> 00:31:16,558
who scammed him out of all his money.

421
00:31:16,559 --> 00:31:19,079
The CP fans could have easily
dug up that he wasn't Ji Zongjun.

422
00:31:19,119 --> 00:31:21,400
So he found a bunch of 'Ji Zongjuns'

423
00:31:21,512 --> 00:31:22,969
to stage that kind of situation.

424
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:23,680
No wonder.

425
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:24,519
He thinks he's so clever.

426
00:31:24,599 --> 00:31:25,959
I feel like he's not even human anymore.

427
00:31:25,960 --> 00:31:26,720
He's also too clever for his own good.

428
00:31:26,721 --> 00:31:29,720
He's like a husk of a person
with its soul scooped out.

429
00:31:29,759 --> 00:31:30,880
I've said it before.

430
00:31:31,519 --> 00:31:32,679
That movie will be

431
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,896
the peak Shi Yuhao will look
up to for the rest of his life.

432
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:35,279
He'll never surpass it.

433
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:36,440
You seem to be enjoying this.

434
00:31:36,559 --> 00:31:37,959
I'm not enjoying it because of him.

435
00:31:38,319 --> 00:31:39,160
Is Qingtian there?

436
00:31:39,161 --> 00:31:40,319
But Qinglang is different.

437
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,559
He'll go much higher

438
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,758
because he knows how to be grateful.

439
00:31:42,759 --> 00:31:43,919
He's talking with Sister Jialin.

440
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:45,400
Only grateful people can go far.

441
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:46,160
No need.

442
00:31:46,161 --> 00:31:47,721
Sister Lan has helped my brother a lot.

443
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:49,000
The livestream mistake...

444
00:31:49,319 --> 00:31:50,000
don't yell at him for it.

445
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:50,799
Of all the people I know...

446
00:31:50,799 --> 00:31:51,519
Okay.

447
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,880
Sister Lan is the most perceptive.

448
00:31:53,559 --> 00:31:54,119
Master.

449
00:31:54,119 --> 00:31:54,400
Hm?

450
00:31:54,401 --> 00:31:56,920
You and Sister Lan are old friends, right?

451
00:31:57,400 --> 00:31:59,519
Yeah, we've known each other for 15 years.

452
00:31:59,599 --> 00:32:01,519
For a person to stay
the same for 15 years...

453
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:02,920
that's so difficult.

454
00:32:05,170 --> 00:32:07,870
[What kind of comment did you
leave? None of them seem like you.]

455
00:32:12,196 --> 00:32:14,529
[Take your time to find it.]

456
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:18,319
No matter her position,

457
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:20,400
Xing Lan has always stayed true to herself.

458
00:32:21,079 --> 00:32:23,079
The changing times don't sway her.

459
00:32:23,103 --> 00:32:25,363
[He's trying to call
Changyang but can't connect]

460
00:32:27,759 --> 00:32:28,759
It's the Dragon Elephant Festival,

461
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:30,000
so we can't serve meat.

462
00:32:30,119 --> 00:32:31,119
I've been eating a lot of meat lately.

463
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,335
A vegetarian meal is a nice change.

464
00:32:32,359 --> 00:32:33,976
It's a good thing it's the
Dragon Elephant Festival.

465
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:35,518
Otherwise, you would've
had to slaughter a pig for us.

466
00:32:35,519 --> 00:32:36,759
That would be too much trouble.

467
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:38,920
Oh.

468
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,079
No need. Our local
piglets are delicious.

469
00:32:43,279 --> 00:32:45,960
I'll make sure you all get
to try some after the festival.

470
00:32:47,519 --> 00:32:48,519
Please, have a seat.

471
00:33:29,519 --> 00:33:31,960
Even if you take pictures, we
won't allow you to post them.

472
00:33:34,519 --> 00:33:35,480
If you post them without our permission,

473
00:33:35,481 --> 00:33:36,720
we can sue you.

474
00:33:44,519 --> 00:33:46,000
Welcome, welcome.

475
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,079
You took this photo, right?

476
00:33:54,119 --> 00:33:55,279
It's a great shot.

477
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:58,799
Next time, I can have the
lighting crew set up some lights

478
00:33:59,119 --> 00:34:00,640
so you can get a clearer picture.

479
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,599
But if it were clearer,

480
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:06,279
you'd be able to see the
person in the photo isn't you.

481
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:08,400
I've saved the picture.

482
00:34:09,119 --> 00:34:10,119
Thank you.

483
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:11,880
I like it a lot.

484
00:34:12,960 --> 00:34:13,960
He likes it a lot too.

485
00:34:16,960 --> 00:34:17,960
Come on.

486
00:34:18,719 --> 00:34:19,719
Yuhao.

487
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,840
Aren't you going to
toast Sister Jialin first?

488
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:27,159
Come on, Sister Jialin.

489
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,360
You're just the same as
you were seven years ago.

490
00:34:36,719 --> 00:34:37,800
Still playing favorites.

491
00:34:39,519 --> 00:34:40,880
Only doing styling for Qinglang.

492
00:34:42,599 --> 00:34:43,599
Now that's not fair.

493
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:46,240
How was I supposed to know
you'd show up unannounced today?

494
00:35:02,760 --> 00:35:03,760
I'm heading out.

495
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:05,320
Just say I went to the restroom.

496
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:10,480
Where did he go?

497
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:11,800
To the restroom.

498
00:35:36,199 --> 00:35:37,360
So much stuff.

499
00:35:38,119 --> 00:35:39,119
To elope with you.

500
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:51,000
Aren't you going to ask where we're going?

501
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:53,559
I'm the one being kidnapped here.

502
00:35:53,719 --> 00:35:54,919
I don't have the right to ask.

503
00:36:06,719 --> 00:36:09,199
If you're tired, you can sleep.
We've still got an hour to go.

504
00:37:52,519 --> 00:37:54,960
When you stand here, don't
all your troubles just melt away?

505
00:38:02,599 --> 00:38:05,320
And the sunrise tomorrow
morning will be spectacular.

506
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:07,800
This is my secret spot.

507
00:38:08,199 --> 00:38:09,679
I haven't brought anyone else here.

508
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,280
Is there more?

509
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:20,080
You need a nest egg to elope.

510
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,960
I don't think I loved you
this much in my past life.

511
00:38:31,199 --> 00:38:32,679
Because it wasn't enough,

512
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,760
I have to make it all
up to you in this life.

513
00:39:37,800 --> 00:39:38,800
Ah.

514
00:40:03,519 --> 00:40:04,519
Hey.

515
00:40:04,920 --> 00:40:06,920
No one saw me sneak out, right?

516
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:08,760
[No one] other than me.

517
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:19,280
It's cold. Hurry back inside.

518
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:21,880
Come out and take a picture with me.

519
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:25,200
If we take one, do you dare post it?

520
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,400
Of course.

521
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,880
I dont' think my brother has a signal.

522
00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:00,119
How's this one?

523
00:43:00,760 --> 00:43:01,760
Post it.

524
00:43:02,119 --> 00:43:03,880
Fine, I'll send it to you.

525
00:43:05,519 --> 00:43:06,519
You're cheating!

526
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:08,000
Yep.

527
00:43:08,679 --> 00:43:09,919
Well, it's not like I'm scared.

528
00:43:10,079 --> 00:43:11,199
Then what are you scared of?

529
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,079
Losing you.

530
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:18,320
